WEBVTT

0
00:01:28.265 --> 00:01:30.309
<i>October is inventory time</i>.

2
00:01:30.392 --> 00:01:33.979
<i>So right now, Statler Toyota is making
the best deals of the year,</i>

3
00:01:34.004 --> 00:01:36.131
<i>on all 1985-model Toyotas.</i>

4
00:01:36.273 --> 00:01:37.883
<i>You won't find a better car,</i>

5
00:01:37.884 --> 00:01:41.262
<i>at a better price with better service
anywhere in Hill Valley.</i>

6
00:01:41.511 --> 00:01:44.155
<i>That's Statler Toyota
in downtown Hill Valley.</i>

7
00:01:47.576 --> 00:01:50.212
<i>The Senate is expected
to vote on this today.</i>

8
00:01:50.496 --> 00:01:51.890
<i>In other news,</i>

9
00:01:52.191 --> 00:01:54.923
<i>officials at the Pacific Nuclear
research facility,</i>

10
00:01:54.948 --> 00:01:57.620
<i>have denied the rumor
that a case of missing plutonium,</i>

11
00:01:57.621 --> 00:02:00.581
<i>was in fact stolen from their vault
two weeks ago.</i>

12
00:02:00.965 --> 00:02:04.518
<i>A Libyan terrorist group had claimed
responsibility for the alleged theft.</i>

13
00:02:04.843 --> 00:02:07.785
<i>However, officials now attribute
the discrepancy,</i>

14
00:02:07.879 --> 00:02:09.477
<i>to a simple clerical error.</i>

15
00:02:09.932 --> 00:02:12.182
<i>The FBI, which is investigating
the matter,</i>

16
00:02:12.272 --> 00:02:13.502
<i>had no comment.</i>

17
00:02:55.436 --> 00:02:56.232
Hey Doc?

18
00:02:59.269 --> 00:03:00.084
Doc?

19
00:03:01.563 --> 00:03:02.807
Hello!
Anybody home?

20
00:03:03.654 --> 00:03:04.689
Einstein, come here boy.

21
00:03:06.441 --> 00:03:07.918
What's going on?
Oh, God.

22
00:03:09.834 --> 00:03:10.625
Jesus!

23
00:03:11.785 --> 00:03:13.278
That is disgusting.

24
00:03:13.458 --> 00:03:14.841
Where the hell is he?

25
00:04:39.373 --> 00:04:40.374
Rock 'n' roll.

26
00:04:49.008 --> 00:04:50.422
Yo.
<i>Marty is that you?</i>

27
00:04:50.509 --> 00:04:51.603
Hey. Hey Doc.

28
00:04:52.104 --> 00:04:53.023
Where are you?

29
00:04:53.095 --> 00:04:54.195
<i>Thank God I have found you. Listen.</i>

30
00:04:54.196 --> 00:04:56.540
<i>Can you meet me at Twin Pines
Mall tonight at 1:15.</i>

31
00:04:56.565 --> 00:04:58.226
<i>I made a breakthrough,
I will need your assistance.</i>

32
00:04:58.302 --> 00:05:00.279
Wait, wait a moment.
1:15 in the morning?

33
00:05:00.304 --> 00:05:01.804
<i>Yeah!</i>
Doc, what's going on?

34
00:05:02.463 --> 00:05:03.523
Where you been all week?

35
00:05:03.748 --> 00:05:04.347
<i>Working.</i>

36
00:05:04.448 --> 00:05:05.848
Where is Einstein, he is with you?

37
00:05:06.060 --> 00:05:07.260
<i>Yeah, he is right here.</i>

38
00:05:07.618 --> 00:05:10.079
You know Doc, you left your
equipment on all week.

39
00:05:10.404 --> 00:05:11.499
<i>My equipment?</i>

40
00:05:11.800 --> 00:05:12.848
<i>That reminds me Marty.</i>

41
00:05:13.073 --> 00:05:14.639
<i>You better not hook
up to the amplifier.</i>

42
00:05:14.663 --> 00:05:16.838
<i>There is a slight possibility of overload.</i>

43
00:05:16.863 --> 00:05:17.596
Yeah.

44
00:05:18.170 --> 00:05:19.894
I will keep that in mind.
<i>Good.</i>

45
00:05:20.041 --> 00:05:21.983
<i>I will see you tonight.
Don't forget now,</i>

46
00:05:21.984 --> 00:05:24.635
<i>1:15 a.m Twin Pines Mall.</i>
Right.

47
00:05:31.508 --> 00:05:33.138
<i>Are those my clocks I hear?</i>

48
00:05:33.381 --> 00:05:34.075
Yeah.

49
00:05:34.208 --> 00:05:36.290
It's 8:00. clock.

50
00:05:36.639 --> 00:05:37.453
<i>Perfect!</i>

51
00:05:37.477 --> 00:05:38.682
<i>My experiment worked!</i>

52
00:05:38.707 --> 00:05:41.177
<i>They are all exactly 25 minutes slow!</i>

53
00:05:42.353 --> 00:05:44.113
Wait a minute.
Wait a minute Doc.

54
00:05:44.897 --> 00:05:47.191
Are you telling me that it's 8:25?

55
00:05:47.216 --> 00:05:48.216
<i>Precisely.</i>

56
00:05:48.769 --> 00:05:49.703
Damn!

57
00:05:50.444 --> 00:05:51.821
I am late for school.

58
00:06:51.797 --> 00:06:52.633
Oh, Jennifer.

59
00:06:52.658 --> 00:06:54.658
Marty don't go this way,
Strickland is looking for you.

60
00:06:54.717 --> 00:06:56.773
If you get caught, it will be
four tardies in a row.

61
00:06:59.054 --> 00:07:00.748
Alright, come on.
I think we are safe.

62
00:07:01.432 --> 00:07:03.232
You know this time it was not my fault.

63
00:07:03.595 --> 00:07:05.904
The doc set all his clocks
25 minutes slow.

64
00:07:05.929 --> 00:07:06.794
Doc?

65
00:07:07.247 --> 00:07:10.760
Am I to understand you are still hanging
around with Dr. Emmett Brown McFly?

66
00:07:12.354 --> 00:07:13.998
Tardy slip for you, Miss Parker.

67
00:07:15.112 --> 00:07:18.082
And one for you McFly.
I believe that's four in a row.

68
00:07:18.824 --> 00:07:21.485
Let me give you a nickel's worth
of free advice young man.

69
00:07:21.869 --> 00:07:25.039
This so-called Dr. Brown is dangerous.
He is a real nutcase.

70
00:07:25.122 --> 00:07:27.612
Hang around with him,
you will end up in big trouble.

71
00:07:27.637 --> 00:07:28.722
Oh yes, sir.

72
00:07:29.627 --> 00:07:32.596
You got a real attitude problem McFly.
You are a slacker.

73
00:07:33.464 --> 00:07:36.484
You remind me of your father when
he went here, he was a slacker too.

74
00:07:37.676 --> 00:07:39.420
Can I go now, Mr. Strickland?

75
00:07:39.845 --> 00:07:43.556
I noticed your band is on the roster for
the dance auditions after school today.

76
00:07:43.581 --> 00:07:45.081
Why even bother McFly.

77
00:07:45.105 --> 00:07:47.860
You don't have a chance.
You are too much like your old man.

78
00:07:48.062 --> 00:07:51.962
No McFly ever amounted to anything
in the history of Hill Valley.

79
00:07:53.901 --> 00:07:56.055
Yeah, well, history is going to change.

80
00:07:58.364 --> 00:07:59.482
<i>Next please.</i>

81
00:08:05.071 --> 00:08:06.338
Ok, guys, let's rock 'n' roll.

82
00:08:09.083 --> 00:08:10.126
<i>Alright.</i>

83
00:08:11.252 --> 00:08:12.427
<i>We are the...</i>

84
00:08:12.828 --> 00:08:14.110
<i>We are the Pinheads.</i>

85
00:08:15.589 --> 00:08:17.091
<i>One, two, three.</i>

86
00:08:36.694 --> 00:08:37.925
<i>Ok, that's enough.</i>

87
00:08:38.214 --> 00:08:40.302
<i>Thank you, thank you fellas.
Hold it.</i>

88
00:08:40.614 --> 00:08:41.839
<i>Hold it fellas.</i>

89
00:08:42.408 --> 00:08:44.277
<i>I am afraid you are just too darn loud.</i>

90
00:08:45.494 --> 00:08:46.637
<i>Next please.</i>

91
00:08:49.206 --> 00:08:50.683
<i>Next group please.</i>

92
00:08:53.566 --> 00:08:56.144
<i>Re-elect Mayor Goldie Wilson.</i>

93
00:08:56.505 --> 00:08:58.549
<i>Progress is his middle name.</i>

94
00:08:58.574 --> 00:09:00.251
Too loud, I can't believe it.

95
00:09:00.634 --> 00:09:03.387
I am never gonna get a chance
to play in front of anybody.

96
00:09:03.412 --> 00:09:05.773
Marty, one rejection
isn't the end of the world.

97
00:09:05.882 --> 00:09:08.176
No, I just don't think
I am cut out for music.

98
00:09:08.434 --> 00:09:10.321
But you are good Marty.
You are really good.

99
00:09:10.346 --> 00:09:12.278
And this audition tape of yours
is great.

100
00:09:12.303 --> 00:09:14.311
You have got to send it in
to the record company.

101
00:09:14.523 --> 00:09:16.317
It's like Doc's always saying.
Yeah, I know, I know.

102
00:09:16.400 --> 00:09:18.670
If you put your mind to it,
you can accomplish anything.

103
00:09:20.070 --> 00:09:21.764
That's good advice Marty.

104
00:09:21.989 --> 00:09:23.466
Alright, ok Jennifer. What...

105
00:09:23.510 --> 00:09:25.575
What if I send in the tape in
and they don't like it?

106
00:09:25.703 --> 00:09:27.280
I mean what if they say I am no good?

107
00:09:27.545 --> 00:09:30.113
What if they say. Get out of here kid,
you got no future?

108
00:09:30.114 --> 00:09:32.491
I mean I just don't think I can take
that kind of rejection.

109
00:09:33.500 --> 00:09:35.377
Jesus, I am starting to sound
like my old man.

110
00:09:35.502 --> 00:09:36.874
Come on, he is not that bad.

111
00:09:37.278 --> 00:09:39.278
At least he is letting you
borrow the car tomorrow night.

112
00:09:41.550 --> 00:09:43.249
Check out that 4x4.

113
00:09:43.851 --> 00:09:44.921
That is hot.

114
00:09:45.564 --> 00:09:46.820
Ok, back her up.

115
00:09:46.933 --> 00:09:48.132
Someday, Jennifer.

116
00:09:49.084 --> 00:09:50.070
Someday.

117
00:09:50.601 --> 00:09:51.415
Would not it be great,

118
00:09:51.610 --> 00:09:53.679
to take that truck, up to the lake?

119
00:09:55.105 --> 00:09:57.500
Throw a couple of sleeping bags
in the back.

120
00:09:59.443 --> 00:10:01.303
Lie out underneath the stars.

121
00:10:01.596 --> 00:10:02.889
Stop it.
What?

122
00:10:04.156 --> 00:10:05.325
Does your mom know?

123
00:10:05.522 --> 00:10:06.700
About tomorrow night?

124
00:10:06.960 --> 00:10:08.229
No, get out of town.

125
00:10:08.254 --> 00:10:10.229
My mom thinks I am going
camping with the guys.

126
00:10:10.913 --> 00:10:14.013
Look Jennifer, my mother would freak out
if she knew I was going with you.

127
00:10:14.038 --> 00:10:15.860
I would get the standard lecture about...

128
00:10:16.334 --> 00:10:19.404
how she never did that kind of stuff
when she was a kid. I mean look...

129
00:10:19.704 --> 00:10:21.131
I think the woman was born a nun.

130
00:10:21.610 --> 00:10:23.704
She is just trying
to keep you respectable.

131
00:10:24.343 --> 00:10:26.270
She is not doing a very good job.

132
00:10:26.595 --> 00:10:27.646
Terrible.

133
00:10:27.796 --> 00:10:29.587
Save the clock tower!

134
00:10:29.942 --> 00:10:31.541
Save the clock tower!

135
00:10:31.642 --> 00:10:35.288
Mayor Wilson is sponsoring
an initiative to replace that clock.

136
00:10:35.771 --> 00:10:36.865
Thirty years ago,

137
00:10:36.866 --> 00:10:40.050
lightning struck that clock tower
and the clock has not run since.

138
00:10:40.276 --> 00:10:42.800
We at the Hill Valley Preservation Society

139
00:10:42.824 --> 00:10:45.072
think it should be preserved
exactly the way it is.

140
00:10:45.177 --> 00:10:47.112
As part of our history and heritage.

141
00:10:47.137 --> 00:10:48.449
Here we go lady.
There is a quarter.

142
00:10:48.474 --> 00:10:50.514
Thanks you.
Don't forget to take a flyer.

143
00:10:51.187 --> 00:10:53.105
Alright.
Save the clock tower!

144
00:10:55.040 --> 00:10:56.090
Where were we?

145
00:10:57.334 --> 00:10:58.292
Right about here.

146
00:10:58.317 --> 00:10:59.128
Jennifer!

147
00:11:02.464 --> 00:11:03.466
It's my dad.
Right.

148
00:11:03.467 --> 00:11:04.467
I have got to go.

149
00:11:04.925 --> 00:11:06.176
I will call you tonight.

150
00:11:06.387 --> 00:11:07.638
I will be at my grandma's.

151
00:11:07.678 --> 00:11:09.378
Here, let me give you the number.

152
00:11:15.102 --> 00:11:15.717
Bye.

153
00:11:59.355 --> 00:12:02.258
<i>Bravo, Tango, Delta 6-2-9.</i>

154
00:12:02.347 --> 00:12:04.800
<i>Tow for impoundment.
Any unit, please respond.</i>

155
00:12:07.947 --> 00:12:08.806
Perfect.

156
00:12:09.121 --> 00:12:10.556
Just perfect.

157
00:12:16.997 --> 00:12:19.124
I can't believe,
you would loan me your car,

158
00:12:19.215 --> 00:12:21.238
without telling me it had a blind spot.

159
00:12:21.327 --> 00:12:22.612
Please listen...
I could have been killed.

160
00:12:23.128 --> 00:12:24.457
Now, now Biff know,

161
00:12:24.607 --> 00:12:25.778
I never noticed that,

162
00:12:25.802 --> 00:12:28.155
the car had any blind spot,

163
00:12:28.179 --> 00:12:29.552
before when I would drive it.

164
00:12:29.697 --> 00:12:30.815
Hi son.

165
00:12:31.136 --> 00:12:32.730
What, are you blind McFly?

166
00:12:33.013 --> 00:12:35.207
It's there. How else do you explain
that wreck out there?

167
00:12:35.508 --> 00:12:36.205
Biff...

168
00:12:36.554 --> 00:12:38.436
can I, can I assume...

169
00:12:38.811 --> 00:12:41.814
that your insurance is going to pay
for the damage?

170
00:12:41.897 --> 00:12:43.041
My insurance?

171
00:12:43.042 --> 00:12:44.191
It's your car.

172
00:12:44.316 --> 00:12:47.036
Your insurance should pay for.
I wanna know who is going to pay for this?

173
00:12:47.186 --> 00:12:49.262
I spilled beer all over it when the car
smashed into me.

174
00:12:49.263 --> 00:12:50.750
Who is gonna pay my cleaning bill?

175
00:12:51.448 --> 00:12:52.925
And where is my reports?

176
00:12:53.450 --> 00:12:55.265
Well I have not finished those up yet.

177
00:12:55.289 --> 00:12:57.771
You know I-I figured
since they were not due 'til...

178
00:12:57.796 --> 00:12:58.686
Hello?

179
00:12:58.721 --> 00:13:00.575
Hello, anybody home?

180
00:13:01.379 --> 00:13:02.740
Think McFly.
Alright.

181
00:13:02.820 --> 00:13:03.676
Think!

182
00:13:03.816 --> 00:13:05.616
I got to have time to get
them retyped.

183
00:13:05.704 --> 00:13:07.246
But do you realize what would happen,

184
00:13:07.247 --> 00:13:09.717
if I hand in my reports in your handwriting?

185
00:13:10.191 --> 00:13:11.376
I will get fired.

186
00:13:11.773 --> 00:13:13.742
You would not want that to happen,
would you?

187
00:13:14.620 --> 00:13:16.580
Would you?
Of course not Biff.

188
00:13:16.683 --> 00:13:18.426
No I would not want that to happen.

189
00:13:19.242 --> 00:13:22.486
Now look. I will finish those reports
tonight and I...

190
00:13:22.696 --> 00:13:24.889
run them on over first
thing tomorrow alright.

191
00:13:25.013 --> 00:13:26.929
Not too early, I sleep in Saturday.

192
00:13:26.954 --> 00:13:28.350
But why your shoe is untied.

193
00:13:29.452 --> 00:13:31.429
Don't be so gullible McFly.

194
00:13:31.839 --> 00:13:33.716
Got the place fixed up nice, though McFly.

195
00:13:36.076 --> 00:13:38.276
I have your car towed to your house,

196
00:13:38.287 --> 00:13:40.164
and all you got for me is lite beer?

197
00:13:47.705 --> 00:13:49.332
What are you looking at butthead?

198
00:13:52.155 --> 00:13:53.709
Say hi to your mom for me.

199
00:13:56.951 --> 00:13:58.743
I know what you are gonna say son.

200
00:13:59.144 --> 00:14:00.235
And you are right.

201
00:14:01.060 --> 00:14:02.136
You are right.

202
00:14:03.020 --> 00:14:03.821
But...

203
00:14:04.813 --> 00:14:07.499
Biff just happens to be my supervisor
and I am...

204
00:14:08.100 --> 00:14:11.537
afraid I am just not very good
at confrontations.

205
00:14:12.738 --> 00:14:14.331
But the car Dad.

206
00:14:16.325 --> 00:14:18.702
I mean, he wrecked it.
He totaled it.

207
00:14:19.912 --> 00:14:21.956
I needed that car tomorrow night Dad.

208
00:14:21.981 --> 00:14:24.534
Do you have any idea how
important this was to me?

209
00:14:24.559 --> 00:14:25.458
Do you have any clue?

210
00:14:25.459 --> 00:14:27.603
I know and all I can say is I am...

211
00:14:28.671 --> 00:14:29.730
I am sorry.

212
00:14:30.422 --> 00:14:31.949
Believe me Marty,

213
00:14:32.174 --> 00:14:34.661
you are better off without having
to worry about all the...

214
00:14:34.912 --> 00:14:37.065
aggravation and headaches...

215
00:14:37.898 --> 00:14:39.198
playing at that dance.

216
00:14:39.223 --> 00:14:40.631
He is absolutely right Marty.

217
00:14:40.854 --> 00:14:42.247
The last thing you need...

218
00:14:42.388 --> 00:14:43.477
is headaches.

219
00:14:51.318 --> 00:14:52.318
Kids,

220
00:14:52.703 --> 00:14:55.105
we are going to have to eat
this cake by ourselves.

221
00:14:55.531 --> 00:14:57.708
Your Uncle Joey didn't make parole again.

222
00:15:00.286 --> 00:15:03.039
I think it would be nice
if you all dropped him a line.

223
00:15:03.706 --> 00:15:05.332
Uncle Jailbird Joey?

224
00:15:05.457 --> 00:15:07.001
He is your brother, Mom.

225
00:15:07.026 --> 00:15:10.780
Yeah. It's a major embarrassment,
having an uncle in prison.

226
00:15:11.225 --> 00:15:13.215
We all make mistakes in life children.

227
00:15:13.299 --> 00:15:14.842
Goddamn it.
I am late.

228
00:15:15.036 --> 00:15:16.563
David, watch your mouth!

229
00:15:16.844 --> 00:15:19.188
Come here and kiss your mother
before you go.

230
00:15:19.189 --> 00:15:20.900
Come here.
Come on Mom make it fast.

231
00:15:21.555 --> 00:15:22.555
I will miss my bus.

232
00:15:23.058 --> 00:15:24.226
See you later Pop.

233
00:15:25.477 --> 00:15:26.954
Time to change that oil.

234
00:15:30.524 --> 00:15:31.525
Hey Marty.

235
00:15:32.276 --> 00:15:34.174
I am not your answering service.

236
00:15:34.198 --> 00:15:36.530
While you were outside
pouting over the car.

237
00:15:36.655 --> 00:15:38.608
Jennifer Parker called you twice.

238
00:15:38.758 --> 00:15:40.301
I don't like her Marty.

239
00:15:40.326 --> 00:15:43.585
Any girl who calls up a boy
is just asking for trouble.

240
00:15:43.704 --> 00:15:46.358
Mom, there is nothing wrong
with calling a boy.

241
00:15:46.665 --> 00:15:48.114
I think it's terrible.

242
00:15:48.615 --> 00:15:50.199
Girls chasing boys.

243
00:15:50.586 --> 00:15:53.723
When I was your age,
I never chased a boy or called a boy.

244
00:15:54.006 --> 00:15:56.550
Or sat in a parked car with a boy.

245
00:15:57.108 --> 00:15:59.535
Then how am I ever supposed
to meet anybody?

246
00:16:00.763 --> 00:16:02.729
Well, it will just happen.

247
00:16:03.265 --> 00:16:04.916
Like the way I met your father.

248
00:16:05.684 --> 00:16:08.471
That was so stupid.
Grandpa hit him with the car.

249
00:16:09.104 --> 00:16:10.564
It was meant to be.

250
00:16:11.596 --> 00:16:12.596
Anyway...

251
00:16:13.567 --> 00:16:15.132
if Grandpa had not hit him,

252
00:16:15.156 --> 00:16:16.987
then none of you would have been born.

253
00:16:17.012 --> 00:16:18.197
Yeah, well...

254
00:16:18.739 --> 00:16:22.159
I still don't understand what Dad was
doing in the middle of the street.

255
00:16:22.184 --> 00:16:23.450
What was it, George?

256
00:16:23.551 --> 00:16:24.745
Bird-watching?

257
00:16:24.828 --> 00:16:25.794
What Lorraine?

258
00:16:26.059 --> 00:16:26.930
What?

259
00:16:27.456 --> 00:16:29.469
Anyway, your Grandpa hit him
with the car...

260
00:16:30.459 --> 00:16:32.286
and brought him into the house.

261
00:16:33.545 --> 00:16:35.422
He seemed so helpless.

262
00:16:38.217 --> 00:16:39.677
Like a little lost puppy,

263
00:16:39.777 --> 00:16:41.278
and my heart just went out to him.

264
00:16:41.303 --> 00:16:44.473
Yea, Mom, we know.
You have told us this story a million times.

265
00:16:44.474 --> 00:16:45.775
You felt sorry for him.

266
00:16:45.870 --> 00:16:47.414
So you decided to go with him,

267
00:16:47.438 --> 00:16:49.166
to the Fish Under the Sea dance.

268
00:16:49.191 --> 00:16:52.094
No, no. It was the Enchantment
Under the Sea dance.

269
00:16:53.148 --> 00:16:54.379
Our first date.

270
00:16:54.980 --> 00:16:56.335
I will never forget it.

271
00:16:56.735 --> 00:16:59.406
It was the night of that terrible
thunderstorm, remember George?

272
00:17:03.075 --> 00:17:06.662
Your father kissed me
for the first time on that dance floor.

273
00:17:08.749 --> 00:17:10.376
It was then that I realized...

274
00:17:11.166 --> 00:17:13.558
that I was going to spend
the rest of my life with him.

275
00:17:17.784 --> 00:17:18.883
Oh, no.

276
00:17:43.073 --> 00:17:44.073
Hello.

277
00:17:44.103 --> 00:17:45.597
<i>Marty, you didn't fall asleep, did you?</i>

278
00:17:45.621 --> 00:17:46.737
No I... Doc.

279
00:17:48.273 --> 00:17:49.017
No.

280
00:17:49.228 --> 00:17:50.671
No, don't, don't be silly.

281
00:17:51.123 --> 00:17:52.604
<i>Listen, this is very important.</i>

282
00:17:52.628 --> 00:17:54.001
<i>I forgot my video camera.</i>

283
00:17:54.026 --> 00:17:56.357
<i>Can you stop by my place and pick
it up on your way to the mall?</i>

284
00:17:56.871 --> 00:17:57.868
Yeah.

285
00:17:58.174 --> 00:17:59.845
I am... I am on my way.

286
00:18:23.948 --> 00:18:25.037
Einstein!

287
00:18:25.138 --> 00:18:26.869
Hey Einstein!
Where is the doc, boy?

288
00:19:20.897 --> 00:19:21.697
Doc!

289
00:19:23.316 --> 00:19:23.984
Marty!

290
00:19:24.164 --> 00:19:25.395
You made it!
Yeah.

291
00:19:25.860 --> 00:19:27.314
Welcome to my latest experiment.

292
00:19:27.315 --> 00:19:29.639
This is the big one, the one
I have been waiting for all my life.

293
00:19:30.323 --> 00:19:31.542
Well, it's a DeLorean, right?

294
00:19:31.567 --> 00:19:33.401
Bear with me Marty.
All your questions will be answered.

295
00:19:33.426 --> 00:19:35.034
Roll tape and we will proceed.

296
00:19:35.037 --> 00:19:36.594
Oh Doc?
Is that a Devo suit?

297
00:19:36.595 --> 00:19:38.927
Never mind, never mind that now.
Not now. Not now.

298
00:19:39.791 --> 00:19:40.716
Alright, I am ready.

299
00:19:41.132 --> 00:19:41.875
Good evening.

300
00:19:41.986 --> 00:19:43.056
I am Dr. Emmett Brown.

301
00:19:43.081 --> 00:19:45.149
I am standing on the parking
lot at Twin Pines Mall.

302
00:19:45.244 --> 00:19:48.631
It's Saturday morning,
October 26, 1985, 1:18 a.m.

303
00:19:49.008 --> 00:19:50.719
And this is temporal experiment
number one.

304
00:19:51.312 --> 00:19:52.341
Come on, Einie.

305
00:19:52.366 --> 00:19:53.450
Hey, hey, boy, get in there.

306
00:19:53.475 --> 00:19:54.341
That a boy!

307
00:19:54.434 --> 00:19:55.683
In you go. Sit down.

308
00:19:56.473 --> 00:19:58.217
Put your seat belt on.
That's it.

309
00:20:04.282 --> 00:20:05.027
Ok.

310
00:20:07.093 --> 00:20:08.021
Please note...

311
00:20:08.804 --> 00:20:09.876
that Einstein's clock,

312
00:20:09.901 --> 00:20:12.321
is in precise synchronization
with my control watch.

313
00:20:12.949 --> 00:20:14.359
Got it?
Right. Check Doc.

314
00:20:14.384 --> 00:20:15.084
Good.

315
00:20:17.745 --> 00:20:18.832
Have a good trip Einstein.

316
00:20:19.257 --> 00:20:20.257
Watch your head.

317
00:20:26.379 --> 00:20:28.058
You got that thing hooked up to the...

318
00:20:28.223 --> 00:20:28.906
car?

319
00:20:28.931 --> 00:20:30.792
Watch this.
Yeah. Ok.

320
00:20:31.170 --> 00:20:31.988
Got it.

321
00:20:36.472 --> 00:20:37.434
Jesus!

322
00:20:42.520 --> 00:20:44.043
Not me! The car! The car!

323
00:21:01.539 --> 00:21:03.400
If my calculations are correct...

324
00:21:04.375 --> 00:21:06.603
when this baby hits 88 miles per hour...

325
00:21:07.461 --> 00:21:09.439
you are going to see some serious shit.

326
00:21:45.500 --> 00:21:47.010
Watch this!
Watch this!

327
00:22:05.311 --> 00:22:07.105
What did I tell you?

328
00:22:07.730 --> 00:22:11.150
88 miles per hour!

329
00:22:14.278 --> 00:22:19.199
The temporal displacement occurred
exactly 1:20 a.m and 0 seconds!

330
00:22:20.952 --> 00:22:22.512
Ah Jesus Christ!

331
00:22:22.870 --> 00:22:25.389
Jesus Christ Doc!
You disintegrated Einstein!

332
00:22:25.414 --> 00:22:27.759
Calm down Marty.
I didn't disintegrate anything.

333
00:22:28.125 --> 00:22:30.148
The molecular structure of both Einstein

334
00:22:30.172 --> 00:22:32.238
and the car are completely intact.

335
00:22:32.922 --> 00:22:34.298
Then where the hell are they?

336
00:22:34.323 --> 00:22:35.809
The appropriate question is...

337
00:22:36.021 --> 00:22:37.444
When the hell are they?

338
00:22:37.593 --> 00:22:42.056
You see, Einstein has just become
the world's first time traveler.

339
00:22:42.557 --> 00:22:45.376
I sent him into the future.

340
00:22:46.227 --> 00:22:48.504
One minute into the future, to be exact.

341
00:22:48.688 --> 00:22:49.835
At precisely,

342
00:22:49.904 --> 00:22:51.903
1:21 a.m and 0 seconds,

343
00:22:51.928 --> 00:22:54.530
we shall catch up with him
and the time machine.

344
00:22:58.225 --> 00:22:59.038
Wait a minute.

345
00:22:59.220 --> 00:23:00.366
Wait a minute, Doc?

346
00:23:00.629 --> 00:23:01.403
Are...

347
00:23:02.076 --> 00:23:04.279
are you telling me,
you built a time machine...

348
00:23:06.164 --> 00:23:07.324
out of a DeLorean?

349
00:23:07.325 --> 00:23:08.374
The way I see it...

350
00:23:08.499 --> 00:23:10.439
if you are going to build a time machine
into a car,

351
00:23:10.463 --> 00:23:11.945
why not do it with style?

352
00:23:12.277 --> 00:23:13.113
Besides,

353
00:23:13.215 --> 00:23:15.709
the stainless-steel construction
made the flux dispersal...

354
00:23:17.175 --> 00:23:17.749
Look out!

355
00:24:03.421 --> 00:24:04.546
What? What? Is it hot?

356
00:24:04.754 --> 00:24:06.463
It's cold. Damn cold.

357
00:24:09.802 --> 00:24:12.013
Einstein, you little devil!

358
00:24:14.224 --> 00:24:17.773
Einstein's clock is exactly one minute
behind mine and still ticking!

359
00:24:21.606 --> 00:24:23.191
He is alright.
He is fine.

360
00:24:23.333 --> 00:24:25.627
He is completely unaware
that anything happened.

361
00:24:25.652 --> 00:24:28.321
As far as he is concerned,
the trip was instantaneous.

362
00:24:28.404 --> 00:24:30.932
That's why his watch is
exactly one minute behind mine.

363
00:24:30.998 --> 00:24:34.052
He skipped over that minute to instantly
arrive at this moment in time.

364
00:24:34.123 --> 00:24:34.922
Come here.

365
00:24:35.119 --> 00:24:36.697
I will show you how it works.
Alright.

366
00:24:38.915 --> 00:24:39.767
First,

367
00:24:40.013 --> 00:24:41.569
you turn the time circuits on.

368
00:24:45.663 --> 00:24:46.997
This readout tells
you where you are going.

369
00:24:47.022 --> 00:24:48.349
This one tells you where you are.

370
00:24:48.374 --> 00:24:49.758
This one tells you where you were.

371
00:24:49.960 --> 00:24:52.403
You input your destination time
on this keypad.

372
00:24:52.428 --> 00:24:55.115
Say you want to see the signing
of the Declaration of Independence.

373
00:24:58.101 --> 00:24:59.677
Or witness the birth of Christ.

374
00:25:03.147 --> 00:25:04.336
Here is a red-letter date,

375
00:25:04.360 --> 00:25:05.659
in the history of science.

376
00:25:05.942 --> 00:25:08.695
November 5, 1955.

377
00:25:12.448 --> 00:25:13.950
Yes, of course.

378
00:25:13.975 --> 00:25:16.837
November 5, 1955.

379
00:25:17.662 --> 00:25:19.155
Why? I don't get it.
Ok, what happened?

380
00:25:20.540 --> 00:25:22.601
That was the day I invented time travel.

381
00:25:23.334 --> 00:25:24.578
I remember it vividly.

382
00:25:24.961 --> 00:25:27.005
I was standing on the edge of
my toilet, hanging a clock.

383
00:25:27.030 --> 00:25:29.766
The porcelain was wet.
I slipped, hit my head on the edge of the sink.

384
00:25:29.882 --> 00:25:31.759
And when I came to, I had a revelation.

385
00:25:31.901 --> 00:25:32.781
A vision.

386
00:25:32.937 --> 00:25:34.133
A picture in my head.

387
00:25:34.512 --> 00:25:35.709
A picture of this.

388
00:25:36.180 --> 00:25:38.650
This is what makes time travel possible.

389
00:25:39.392 --> 00:25:40.886
The flux capacitor.

390
00:25:41.477 --> 00:25:42.645
Flux capacitor?

391
00:25:42.723 --> 00:25:44.835
It's taken almost 30 years
and my entire family

392
00:25:44.859 --> 00:25:46.753
fortune to realize the vision of that day.

393
00:25:47.817 --> 00:25:49.928
My God, has it been that long?

394
00:25:50.737 --> 00:25:52.552
Things have certainly changed
around here.

395
00:25:54.532 --> 00:25:57.969
I remember when this was all farmland
as far as the eye could see.

396
00:25:59.871 --> 00:26:00.976
Old man Peabody,

397
00:26:01.281 --> 00:26:02.558
owned all of this.

398
00:26:03.426 --> 00:26:04.897
He had this crazy idea,

399
00:26:05.498 --> 00:26:07.183
about breeding pine trees.

400
00:26:11.299 --> 00:26:12.250
This is...

401
00:26:12.425 --> 00:26:14.519
This is heavy-duty Doc.
This is great.

402
00:26:15.220 --> 00:26:17.564
Does it run on regular unleaded gasoline?

403
00:26:17.756 --> 00:26:20.386
Unfortunately no. It requires
something with a little more kick.

404
00:26:20.563 --> 00:26:21.563
Plutonium.

405
00:26:21.697 --> 00:26:22.695
Ah plutonium.

406
00:26:22.719 --> 00:26:23.753
Wait a minute.
Are you...

407
00:26:24.121 --> 00:26:26.339
Are you telling me, this sucker is nuclear?

408
00:26:26.488 --> 00:26:28.525
Hey, hey, hey! Keep rolling.
Keep rolling there.

409
00:26:28.613 --> 00:26:30.306
No, no, no, no.
This sucker is electrical.

410
00:26:30.527 --> 00:26:34.348
But I need a nuclear reaction to generate
the 1.21 gigawatts of electricity I need.

411
00:26:34.373 --> 00:26:37.700
Doc, you don't just walk into a store
and buy plutonium.

412
00:26:38.535 --> 00:26:39.795
Did you rip that off?

413
00:26:42.184 --> 00:26:43.060
Of course.

414
00:26:43.084 --> 00:26:44.851
From a group of Libyan Nationalists.

415
00:26:44.976 --> 00:26:46.214
They wanted me to build them a bomb.

416
00:26:46.334 --> 00:26:48.470
So, I took their plutonium and in
turn gave them a shoddy bomb,

417
00:26:48.495 --> 00:26:50.544
casing full of used pinball machine parts.

418
00:26:50.588 --> 00:26:52.708
Come on. Let's get you a radiation suit.
Jesus!

419
00:26:52.839 --> 00:26:53.839
We must prepare to reload.

420
00:27:23.193 --> 00:27:25.221
It's safe now.
Everything is lead-lined.

421
00:27:27.622 --> 00:27:29.082
Don't lose those tapes now.

422
00:27:29.752 --> 00:27:31.513
I need that, as a record.

423
00:27:31.796 --> 00:27:33.590
Let's put this back here.
There we go.

424
00:27:36.751 --> 00:27:38.061
Almost forgot my luggage.

425
00:27:38.428 --> 00:27:40.787
Who knows if they got
cotton underwear in the future.

426
00:27:41.264 --> 00:27:42.725
I am allergic to all synthetics poducts.

427
00:27:42.975 --> 00:27:44.099
The future?

428
00:27:44.517 --> 00:27:46.178
That's where you are going.
That's right.

429
00:27:46.436 --> 00:27:47.715
25 years in the future.

430
00:27:47.740 --> 00:27:50.440
I have always dreamed of seeing
the future, looking beyond my years,

431
00:27:50.727 --> 00:27:52.308
seeing the progress of mankind.

432
00:27:53.010 --> 00:27:54.010
Why not?

433
00:27:54.300 --> 00:27:57.120
I will also be able to see
who wins the next 25 World Series.

434
00:27:58.573 --> 00:27:59.374
Doc.

435
00:28:00.992 --> 00:28:03.169
Look me up, when you get there.

436
00:28:04.057 --> 00:28:05.101
Indeed I will.

437
00:28:05.624 --> 00:28:06.624
Roll them.

438
00:28:13.004 --> 00:28:13.734
I...

439
00:28:14.257 --> 00:28:15.600
Dr. Emmett Brown...

440
00:28:17.050 --> 00:28:19.719
am about to embark on an historic journey.

441
00:28:21.846 --> 00:28:23.581
What am I thinking of?

442
00:28:23.618 --> 00:28:25.863
I almost forgot to bring extra plutonium.

443
00:28:26.059 --> 00:28:28.603
How do I expect to get back?
One pellet, one trip.

444
00:28:28.628 --> 00:28:30.072
I must be out of my mind.

445
00:28:33.274 --> 00:28:34.301
What is it Einie?

446
00:28:43.409 --> 00:28:44.494
Oh, my God.

447
00:28:45.036 --> 00:28:47.085
They found me. I don't know how,
but they found me.

448
00:28:47.914 --> 00:28:49.019
Run for it Marty!

449
00:28:49.136 --> 00:28:50.218
Who? Who?

450
00:28:50.583 --> 00:28:52.694
Who do you think?
The Libyans!

451
00:28:56.297 --> 00:28:57.540
Holy shit!

452
00:29:01.844 --> 00:29:03.271
I will draw their fire!

453
00:29:11.646 --> 00:29:12.722
Doc, wait!

454
00:29:27.287 --> 00:29:29.380
No!

455
00:29:29.563 --> 00:29:31.057
You bastard!

456
00:29:49.893 --> 00:29:50.893
Go!

457
00:29:51.468 --> 00:29:52.846
Damn Soviet gun.

458
00:29:57.317 --> 00:29:58.317
Go!

459
00:30:39.128 --> 00:30:40.338
Come on, move.

460
00:30:40.854 --> 00:30:41.645
Dammit!

461
00:30:42.846 --> 00:30:43.754
Jesus!

462
00:31:04.467 --> 00:31:05.727
Holy shit!

463
00:31:06.678 --> 00:31:08.924
Let's see if you bastards can do 90.

464
00:32:01.191 --> 00:32:02.097
What is it?

465
00:32:02.734 --> 00:32:03.794
What is it Pa?

466
00:32:04.277 --> 00:32:05.757
Looks like an airplane,

467
00:32:06.386 --> 00:32:07.761
without wings.

468
00:32:08.114 --> 00:32:09.772
That ain't no airplane.

469
00:32:10.073 --> 00:32:11.101
Look.

470
00:32:32.013 --> 00:32:33.013
Don't look!

471
00:32:33.473 --> 00:32:34.273
Listen, look...

472
00:32:47.362 --> 00:32:48.216
Hello.

473
00:32:51.699 --> 00:32:52.699
Excuse me.

474
00:32:56.496 --> 00:32:57.784
Sorry about your barn.

475
00:33:01.101 --> 00:33:04.354
It's already mutated into human form,
shoot it!

476
00:33:06.714 --> 00:33:09.092
Take that, you mutated son of a bitch!

477
00:33:13.471 --> 00:33:14.471
Wait!

478
00:33:17.141 --> 00:33:18.626
Shoot it Pa!

479
00:33:21.145 --> 00:33:22.478
My pine!

480
00:33:22.479 --> 00:33:24.048
Why you...

481
00:33:26.234 --> 00:33:27.746
You space bastard!

482
00:33:28.008 --> 00:33:29.480
You killed our pine!

483
00:33:34.033 --> 00:33:35.610
Alright. Alright.
Ok McFly.

484
00:33:35.994 --> 00:33:38.204
Get a grip on yourself.
It's all a dream.

485
00:33:38.374 --> 00:33:41.210
It's just a very intense dream.

486
00:34:24.125 --> 00:34:25.563
Listen, you got to help me.

487
00:34:25.587 --> 00:34:27.295
Don't stop Wilbur! Don't!

488
00:34:29.945 --> 00:34:30.843
It can't be.

489
00:34:37.430 --> 00:34:38.500
This is nuts.

490
00:34:43.186 --> 00:34:43.937
Come on.

491
00:34:45.480 --> 00:34:46.269
Perfect.

492
00:36:41.004 --> 00:36:44.725
<i>Remember, fellow citizens,
the future is in your hands.</i>

493
00:36:45.008 --> 00:36:48.679
<i>If you believe in progress,
re-elect Mayor Red Thomas.</i>

494
00:36:48.887 --> 00:36:50.931
<i>Progress is his middle name.</i>

495
00:36:51.056 --> 00:36:53.500
<i>Mayor Red Thomas' progress platform,</i>

496
00:36:53.616 --> 00:36:56.076
<i>means more jobs, better education,</i>

497
00:36:56.311 --> 00:36:58.998
<i>bigger civic improvements
and lower taxes.</i>

498
00:36:59.481 --> 00:37:00.586
<i>On election day,</i>

499
00:37:00.611 --> 00:37:03.041
<i>cast your vote for a proven leader.</i>

500
00:37:03.277 --> 00:37:05.271
<i>Re-elect Mayor Red Thomas.</i>

501
00:37:08.907 --> 00:37:10.368
This has got to be a dream.

502
00:37:27.885 --> 00:37:30.012
Hey kid.
What you do, you jump ship?

503
00:37:30.929 --> 00:37:31.561
What?

504
00:37:31.796 --> 00:37:33.468
What's with the life preserver?

505
00:37:38.645 --> 00:37:39.933
I want to use the phone.

506
00:37:40.870 --> 00:37:42.027
It's in the back.

507
00:37:45.152 --> 00:37:45.925
Brown.

508
00:37:48.663 --> 00:37:50.252
Great.
You are alive.

509
00:38:02.252 --> 00:38:03.370
Come on.

510
00:38:11.011 --> 00:38:14.857
Do you know where 1640 Riverside...
You gonna order something kid?

511
00:38:17.017 --> 00:38:17.845
Yeah.

512
00:38:18.570 --> 00:38:19.670
Give me...
Give me a Tab.

513
00:38:20.437 --> 00:38:22.598
Tab? I can't give you a tab
unless you order something.

514
00:38:22.882 --> 00:38:24.359
Right. Give me a Pepsi Free.

515
00:38:24.929 --> 00:38:27.040
You want a Pepsi pal,
you are going to pay for it.

516
00:38:27.945 --> 00:38:30.431
Just give me something
without any sugar in it, ok?

517
00:38:31.068 --> 00:38:32.361
Something without sugar.

518
00:38:40.551 --> 00:38:41.619
Hey McFly.

519
00:38:44.503 --> 00:38:45.708
What do you think you are doing?

520
00:38:46.830 --> 00:38:47.708
Biff.

521
00:38:48.424 --> 00:38:50.884
Hey I am talking to you McFly,
you Irish bug!

522
00:38:51.323 --> 00:38:53.390
Hey Biff, hey Guys.
How are you doing?

523
00:38:53.415 --> 00:38:54.815
You got my homework finished McFly?

524
00:38:55.637 --> 00:38:58.409
Well actually, I figured since it
was not due 'til Monday...

525
00:38:58.434 --> 00:39:00.013
Hello? Hello?

526
00:39:00.114 --> 00:39:01.170
Anybody home?

527
00:39:01.171 --> 00:39:02.944
Hey think McFly.

528
00:39:02.945 --> 00:39:03.689
Think!

529
00:39:03.772 --> 00:39:05.549
I got to have time to recopy it.

530
00:39:05.733 --> 00:39:09.186
You realize what would happen if I hand in
my homework in your handwriting?

531
00:39:09.437 --> 00:39:10.947
I will get kicked out of school.

532
00:39:11.405 --> 00:39:13.449
You would not want that to happen,
would you?

533
00:39:16.118 --> 00:39:17.828
Would you?
Now, of course not Biff.

534
00:39:17.853 --> 00:39:19.330
No.
I would not want that to happen.

535
00:39:19.955 --> 00:39:21.341
What are you looking at, butthead?

536
00:39:21.519 --> 00:39:23.378
Biff, get a load of this guy is life preserver.

537
00:39:24.001 --> 00:39:25.766
Dork thinks he is going to drown.
Yeah.

538
00:39:25.791 --> 00:39:27.368
How about my homework McFly?

539
00:39:28.797 --> 00:39:30.124
Ok Biff. Well...

540
00:39:30.591 --> 00:39:32.697
I will finish that up tonight and then...

541
00:39:32.722 --> 00:39:35.235
I will bring it over first thing
tomorrow morning.

542
00:39:35.554 --> 00:39:38.558
Not too early. I sleep in Sundays.
Oh McFly, your shoe is untied!

543
00:39:39.683 --> 00:39:41.727
Don't be so gullible McFly.
Ok.

544
00:39:41.752 --> 00:39:42.869
I don't want to see you in
here again.

545
00:39:42.894 --> 00:39:44.892
Ok. Alright. Bye-bye.

546
00:40:07.417 --> 00:40:08.269
What?

547
00:40:08.480 --> 00:40:09.878
You are George McFly!

548
00:40:10.299 --> 00:40:11.599
Yeah. Who are you?

549
00:40:11.733 --> 00:40:14.956
Say! Why do you let those boys
push you around like that for?

550
00:40:14.981 --> 00:40:16.471
Well, they are bigger than me.

551
00:40:16.496 --> 00:40:19.143
Stand tall boy.
Have some respect for yourself.

552
00:40:19.222 --> 00:40:21.468
Don't you know,
if you let people walk over you now,

553
00:40:21.493 --> 00:40:23.493
they will be walking over you
for the rest of your life.

554
00:40:23.518 --> 00:40:24.388
Look at me.

555
00:40:24.559 --> 00:40:26.916
You think I am gonna spend
the rest of my life in this slop house?

556
00:40:26.941 --> 00:40:28.735
Watch it Goldie.
No sir!

557
00:40:28.760 --> 00:40:31.418
I am gonna make something of myself.
I am going to night school,

558
00:40:31.443 --> 00:40:33.531
and one day, I am going
to be somebody.

559
00:40:33.556 --> 00:40:35.133
That's right.
He is going to be mayor.

560
00:40:35.509 --> 00:40:36.586
Yeah I am...

561
00:40:37.741 --> 00:40:39.118
Mayor!

562
00:40:39.868 --> 00:40:41.932
Now that's a good idea!

563
00:40:41.956 --> 00:40:43.789
I could run for mayor.

564
00:40:43.814 --> 00:40:45.426
A colored mayor.
That will be the day.

565
00:40:45.451 --> 00:40:47.784
You wait and see, Mr. Caruthers.
I will be mayor.

566
00:40:47.809 --> 00:40:50.187
I will be the most powerful man
in Hill Valley,

567
00:40:50.212 --> 00:40:52.081
and I am going to clean up this town.

568
00:40:52.106 --> 00:40:54.333
Good.
You can start by sweeping the floor.

569
00:40:57.636 --> 00:40:59.363
Mayor Goldie Wilson.

570
00:40:59.847 --> 00:41:01.724
I like the sound of that.

571
00:41:14.278 --> 00:41:15.879
Hey, Dad! George!

572
00:41:16.092 --> 00:41:17.698
Hey, you on the bike!

573
00:41:48.979 --> 00:41:50.596
He is a peeping Tom!

574
00:41:56.515 --> 00:41:57.455
Dad!

575
00:42:09.605 --> 00:42:10.305
Hey wait.

576
00:42:10.584 --> 00:42:12.295
Wait a minute.
Who are you?

577
00:42:14.588 --> 00:42:15.384
Stella!

578
00:42:16.009 --> 00:42:18.809
Another one of these damn kids
jumped in front of my car!

579
00:42:19.885 --> 00:42:21.954
Come out here!
Help me take him in the house!

580
00:42:27.653 --> 00:42:28.520
Mom?

581
00:42:29.428 --> 00:42:30.335
That you?

582
00:42:31.414 --> 00:42:32.421
There now.

583
00:42:32.940 --> 00:42:34.226
Just relax.

584
00:42:36.828 --> 00:42:39.498
