for almost nine hours now.

585
00:42:41.818 --> 00:42:42.544
I had a...

586
00:42:42.982 --> 00:42:44.359
horrible nightmare.

587
00:42:45.361 --> 00:42:46.340
I dreamed that I went...

588
00:42:47.015 --> 00:42:48.347
back in time.

589
00:42:48.819 --> 00:42:50.031
It was terrible.

590
00:42:50.991 --> 00:42:51.770
Well...

591
00:42:52.805 --> 00:42:56.247
you are safe and sound now
back in good old 1955.

592
00:42:57.456 --> 00:42:58.874
1955?

593
00:43:03.671 --> 00:43:04.698
You are my...

594
00:43:05.074 --> 00:43:06.097
You are my...

595
00:43:06.507 --> 00:43:07.697
My name is Lorraine.

596
00:43:08.676 --> 00:43:10.182
Lorraine Baines?

597
00:43:10.548 --> 00:43:11.400
Yeah.

598
00:43:12.638 --> 00:43:13.881
But you are...

599
00:43:14.265 --> 00:43:15.327
Just so...

600
00:43:15.787 --> 00:43:16.624
You are so...

601
00:43:18.296 --> 00:43:19.172
Thin!

602
00:43:19.270 --> 00:43:22.156
Just relax Calvin.
You got a big bruise on your head.

603
00:43:26.819 --> 00:43:27.920
Where are my pants?

604
00:43:28.779 --> 00:43:29.670
Over there.

605
00:43:30.713 --> 00:43:31.940
On my hope chest.

606
00:43:33.868 --> 00:43:36.404
I have never seen purple
underwear before Calvin.

607
00:43:37.079 --> 00:43:39.882
Calvin? Why-why do you keep
calling me Calvin?

608
00:43:40.166 --> 00:43:41.437
That is your name, isn't it?

609
00:43:41.694 --> 00:43:42.974
Calvin Klein.

610
00:43:43.419 --> 00:43:45.513
It's written all over your underwear.

611
00:43:46.672 --> 00:43:48.449
I guess they call you Cal?

612
00:43:49.347 --> 00:43:50.740
No actually people...

613
00:43:51.833 --> 00:43:52.977
call me Marty.

614
00:43:55.222 --> 00:43:56.844
Pleased to meet you Calvin.

615
00:43:58.559 --> 00:43:59.559
Marty.

616
00:44:01.353 --> 00:44:02.353
Klein.

617
00:44:09.361 --> 00:44:10.623
Do you mind if I sit here?

618
00:44:11.396 --> 00:44:12.615
No. Fine.

619
00:44:12.782 --> 00:44:14.302
No. Good. Fine.

620
00:44:14.473 --> 00:44:15.153
Good.

621
00:44:17.161 --> 00:44:19.261
That's a big bruise you have there.

622
00:44:21.229 --> 00:44:23.323
Lorraine, are you up there?

623
00:44:23.501 --> 00:44:24.977
Oh, my God!
It's my mother!

624
00:44:25.544 --> 00:44:26.368
Quick!

625
00:44:27.016 --> 00:44:28.439
Put your pants back on!

626
00:44:36.806 --> 00:44:38.900
So, tell me Marty,
how long have you been in port?

627
00:44:39.576 --> 00:44:41.744
Excuse me?
I guessed you are a sailor.

628
00:44:41.769 --> 00:44:43.730
That's why you wear that life preserver.

629
00:44:44.355 --> 00:44:45.531
Coast guard.

630
00:44:45.619 --> 00:44:46.444
Sam,

631
00:44:46.785 --> 00:44:49.094
here is the young man you hit
with your car out there.

632
00:44:49.219 --> 00:44:50.476
He is alright.
Thank God.

633
00:44:50.477 --> 00:44:52.630
What were you doing in the middle
of the street, a kid your age?

634
00:44:52.655 --> 00:44:54.618
Don't pay attention to him.
He is in one of his moods.

635
00:44:54.643 --> 00:44:57.501
Sam, you quit fiddling with that thing.
Come in here to dinner.

636
00:44:57.758 --> 00:44:59.535
Now let's see.
You already know Lorraine.

637
00:44:59.883 --> 00:45:02.382
This is Milton, this is Sally...

638
00:45:02.498 --> 00:45:03.769
that's Toby,

639
00:45:03.793 --> 00:45:06.510
and over there
in the playpen is little baby Joey.

640
00:45:08.712 --> 00:45:10.373
So, you are my uncle Joey.

641
00:45:11.590 --> 00:45:13.568
Better get used to these bars kid.

642
00:45:14.093 --> 00:45:18.205
Yes. Joey just loves being in his playpen.

643
00:45:18.431 --> 00:45:21.817
He cries whenever we take him out,
so we leave him in there all the time.

644
00:45:22.056 --> 00:45:24.433
Well, Marty, I hope you like meatloaf.

645
00:45:24.458 --> 00:45:26.228
Well listen, I really ought to...

646
00:45:26.587 --> 00:45:27.731
Sit here Marty.

647
00:45:28.524 --> 00:45:32.413
Sam, stop fiddling with that thing
and come in here and eat your dinner.

648
00:45:34.699 --> 00:45:36.210
Look at it roll.

649
00:45:36.574 --> 00:45:38.977
Now we can watch
Jackie Gleason while we eat.

650
00:45:47.668 --> 00:45:49.116
Our first television set.

651
00:45:49.323 --> 00:45:50.895
Dad just picked it up today.

652
00:45:51.964 --> 00:45:53.191
Do you have a television?

653
00:45:54.024 --> 00:45:55.404
Yeah, you know we have...

654
00:45:55.833 --> 00:45:56.941
two of them.

655
00:45:58.324 --> 00:45:59.691
You must be rich.

656
00:45:59.972 --> 00:46:03.935
Oh honey, he is teasing you.
Nobody has two television sets.

657
00:46:08.823 --> 00:46:09.536
Hey.

658
00:46:10.107 --> 00:46:13.027
Hey. I have seen this one.
I have seen this one, this is a classic.

659
00:46:13.052 --> 00:46:15.655
This is where Ralph dresses up
as a man from space.

660
00:46:16.363 --> 00:46:17.794
What do you mean, you have seen this?

661
00:46:18.207 --> 00:46:19.433
It's brand-new.

662
00:46:19.867 --> 00:46:21.013
Yeah, well, I saw it on a...

663
00:46:21.240 --> 00:46:22.498
rerun.

664
00:46:22.953 --> 00:46:23.924
What's a rerun?

665
00:46:24.872 --> 00:46:26.033
You will find out.

666
00:46:26.457 --> 00:46:28.952
You know Marty, you look so familiar to me.

667
00:46:28.977 --> 00:46:30.537
Do I know your mother?

668
00:46:32.046 --> 00:46:33.806
Yeah, I think maybe you do.

669
00:46:34.173 --> 00:46:37.367
Oh, then I want to give her a call.
I don't want her to worry about you.

670
00:46:37.392 --> 00:46:38.460
You can't.

671
00:46:39.828 --> 00:46:41.557
That is, nobody here...

672
00:46:42.158 --> 00:46:43.124
nobody home.

673
00:46:45.726 --> 00:46:46.507
Yet.

674
00:46:49.471 --> 00:46:50.339
Listen.

675
00:46:50.564 --> 00:46:53.009
Do you... Do you know where
Riverside Drive is?

676
00:46:53.234 --> 00:46:55.673
It's on the other end of town.
A block past Maple.

677
00:46:55.774 --> 00:46:56.854
East end of town.

678
00:46:57.395 --> 00:46:58.829
Wait a minute, a block past Maple.

679
00:46:58.854 --> 00:47:01.156
That's John F. Kennedy Drive.

680
00:47:02.284 --> 00:47:03.925
Who the hell is John F. Kennedy?

681
00:47:04.229 --> 00:47:05.198
Mother?

682
00:47:06.288 --> 00:47:08.716
With Marty's parents out of town,

683
00:47:09.458 --> 00:47:11.531
don't you think he ought
to spend the night?

684
00:47:11.961 --> 00:47:14.238
I mean after all,
Dad almost killed him with the car.

685
00:47:14.463 --> 00:47:16.024
That's true Marty.

686
00:47:16.632 --> 00:47:18.379
I think maybe you should spend the night.

687
00:47:18.403 --> 00:47:20.114
I think you are our responsibility.

688
00:47:20.139 --> 00:47:21.484
Well, gee, I don't know.

689
00:47:21.549 --> 00:47:23.448
He can sleep in my room.

690
00:47:24.181 --> 00:47:26.082
I got to go!
I got to go!

691
00:47:26.132 --> 00:47:28.470
Thanks very much, it was wonderful.
You were all great...

692
00:47:28.695 --> 00:47:29.695
See you all later.

693
00:47:30.920 --> 00:47:32.020
Too much later.

694
00:47:36.485 --> 00:47:38.813
He is a very strange young man.

695
00:47:39.193 --> 00:47:40.269
He is an idiot.

696
00:47:40.823 --> 00:47:42.040
Comes from upbringing.

697
00:47:42.230 --> 00:47:43.798
His parents are probably idiots too.

698
00:47:44.910 --> 00:47:47.681
Lorraine, you ever have a kid
who acts that way, I will disown you.

699
00:48:26.377 --> 00:48:27.183
Doc?

700
00:48:28.222 --> 00:48:29.176
Don't say a word.

701
00:48:30.449 --> 00:48:31.138
Doc.

702
00:48:31.163 --> 00:48:32.284
I don't wanna know your name.

703
00:48:32.309 --> 00:48:33.634
I don't want to know anything
bout you.

704
00:48:33.659 --> 00:48:34.559
Listen Doc...
Quiet!

705
00:48:34.729 --> 00:48:35.417
Doc.

706
00:48:35.418 --> 00:48:36.918
Doc, it's me Marty.
Don't tell me anything.

707
00:48:37.003 --> 00:48:38.026
Doc, you got to help...
Quiet.

708
00:48:38.089 --> 00:48:38.770
Quiet.

709
00:48:41.924 --> 00:48:43.526
I am going to read your thoughts.

710
00:48:44.010 --> 00:48:45.958
Let's see now. You have come here...

711
00:48:46.041 --> 00:48:47.655
from a great distance?

712
00:48:47.680 --> 00:48:48.805
Yeah.
Exactly.

713
00:48:48.806 --> 00:48:49.815
Don't tell me!

714
00:48:50.683 --> 00:48:53.518
You want me to buy a subscription
to the Saturday Evening Post.

715
00:48:53.603 --> 00:48:54.215
No.

716
00:48:54.240 --> 00:48:56.023
Not a word. Not a word.
Not a word now!

717
00:48:56.272 --> 00:48:57.072
Quiet.

718
00:48:59.515 --> 00:49:00.560
Donations.

719
00:49:01.123 --> 00:49:02.562
You want me to make a donation...

720
00:49:03.279 --> 00:49:05.530
to the Coast Guard Youth Auxiliary.

721
00:49:06.115 --> 00:49:06.900
Doc.

722
00:49:09.035 --> 00:49:10.233
I am from the future.

723
00:49:11.245 --> 00:49:14.372
I came here in a time machine
you invented.

724
00:49:14.749 --> 00:49:17.281
But now, I need your help
to get back to the year,

725
00:49:17.305 --> 00:49:19.544
1985.

726
00:49:20.921 --> 00:49:22.450
My God.

727
00:49:26.927 --> 00:49:29.137
Do you know what this means?

728
00:49:30.806 --> 00:49:32.490
It means that this...

729
00:49:32.689 --> 00:49:35.202
damn thing doesn't work at all!

730
00:49:35.227 --> 00:49:36.545
Doc, you got to help me.

731
00:49:36.570 --> 00:49:39.064
You are the only one who knows
how your time machine works.

732
00:49:39.649 --> 00:49:40.685
Time machine?

733
00:49:41.980 --> 00:49:43.672
I have not invented any time machine.

734
00:49:45.404 --> 00:49:47.222
Ok. Alright, I will prove it to you.

735
00:49:47.907 --> 00:49:49.289
Look at my driver's license.

736
00:49:49.425 --> 00:49:51.076
Expires 1987.

737
00:49:51.219 --> 00:49:52.720
Look at my birthday, for crying out loud!

738
00:49:52.745 --> 00:49:54.302
I have not even been born yet.

739
00:49:54.830 --> 00:49:55.694
And...

740
00:49:55.974 --> 00:49:57.165
look at this picture.

741
00:49:57.249 --> 00:49:58.888
It's my brother, my sister and me.

742
00:49:59.335 --> 00:50:00.782
Look at her sweatshirt Doc.

743
00:50:00.993 --> 00:50:02.816
Class of 1984?

744
00:50:03.589 --> 00:50:05.720
Pretty mediocre photographic fakery.

745
00:50:05.745 --> 00:50:07.428
They cut off your brother's hair.

746
00:50:08.469 --> 00:50:10.745
I am telling the truth Doc.
You got to believe me.

747
00:50:10.930 --> 00:50:13.014
Then tell me, future boy,

748
00:50:14.183 --> 00:50:16.301
Who is President of the United States...

749
00:50:16.536 --> 00:50:17.954
in 1985?

750
00:50:18.354 --> 00:50:19.454
Ronald Reagan.

751
00:50:19.480 --> 00:50:20.396
Ronald Reagan?

752
00:50:20.670 --> 00:50:21.756
The actor?

753
00:50:23.442 --> 00:50:24.900
Then who is vice president?

754
00:50:24.924 --> 00:50:25.985
Jerry Lewis?

755
00:50:27.154 --> 00:50:28.685
I suppose Jane Wyman,

756
00:50:28.880 --> 00:50:30.804
is the First Lady.
Wait Doc!

757
00:50:30.829 --> 00:50:33.038
And Jack Benny is secretary of the treasury.

758
00:50:33.077 --> 00:50:34.494
Doc, you got to listen to me.

759
00:50:34.678 --> 00:50:36.663
I have had enough practical
jokes for one evening.

760
00:50:36.747 --> 00:50:37.973
Good night, future boy!

761
00:50:37.998 --> 00:50:39.374
No, wait Doc.
Doc.

762
00:50:39.458 --> 00:50:40.331
The bruise.

763
00:50:40.355 --> 00:50:42.311
The bruise on your head,
I know how that happened.

764
00:50:42.336 --> 00:50:43.753
You told me the whole story.

765
00:50:43.838 --> 00:50:46.359
You were standing on your toilet
and you were hanging a clock,

766
00:50:46.384 --> 00:50:48.695
and you fell and you hit
your head on the sink.

767
00:50:48.801 --> 00:50:51.720
That's when you came up with
the idea for the flux capacitor,

768
00:50:51.804 --> 00:50:53.418
which... is what...

769
00:50:53.621 --> 00:50:55.867
makes time travel possible.

770
00:51:08.904 --> 00:51:10.771
There is something wrong with the starter,

771
00:51:11.053 --> 00:51:12.145
so I hid it...

772
00:51:12.426 --> 00:51:13.331
here.

773
00:51:23.586 --> 00:51:25.714
After I fell off my toilet,

774
00:51:26.415 --> 00:51:27.622
I drew this.

775
00:51:31.927 --> 00:51:33.120
The flux capacitor.

776
00:51:51.572 --> 00:51:52.864
It works!

777
00:51:55.409 --> 00:51:56.951
It works!

778
00:51:58.245 --> 00:52:00.855
I finally invent something that works!

779
00:52:01.707 --> 00:52:03.433
You bet your ass it works.

780
00:52:04.752 --> 00:52:06.961
Somehow we have got to sneak
this back to my laboratory.

781
00:52:07.880 --> 00:52:09.498
We have got to get you home!

782
00:52:10.466 --> 00:52:11.658
Ok Doc, this is it.

783
00:52:14.037 --> 00:52:15.349
<i>Never mind that.
Never mind that now.</i>

784
00:52:15.374 --> 00:52:17.315
<i>Never mind that.</i>
What, that's me!

785
00:52:17.857 --> 00:52:19.847
Look at me!
