01:03:28.365 --> 01:03:30.040
Ok. But I don't know what to say.

1050
01:03:30.065 --> 01:03:32.491
Just say anything George.
Say whatever is natural,

1051
01:03:32.516 --> 01:03:34.258
the first thing that comes into your mind.

1052
01:03:35.868 --> 01:03:37.486
Nothing is coming to my mind.

1053
01:03:37.870 --> 01:03:39.579
Jesus George, it's a wonder
I was even born.

1054
01:03:39.604 --> 01:03:40.681
What?
What?

1055
01:03:40.706 --> 01:03:42.200
Nothing. Nothing. Nothing.

1056
01:03:42.675 --> 01:03:43.513
Look,

1057
01:03:44.021 --> 01:03:46.878
tell her destiny brought you together.

1058
01:03:46.903 --> 01:03:50.271
Tell her that she is the most beautiful girl
you have ever seen in the world.

1059
01:03:50.883 --> 01:03:52.242
Girls like that stuff.

1060
01:03:52.896 --> 01:03:54.019
What are you doing George?

1061
01:03:54.020 --> 01:03:56.095
I am writing this down.
This is good stuff.

1062
01:03:56.120 --> 01:03:57.620
Yeah. Ok. Let's go.

1063
01:03:57.765 --> 01:03:59.224
Can you take care of that?
Right.

1064
01:04:17.743 --> 01:04:18.565
Lou,

1065
01:04:19.399 --> 01:04:20.571
give me a milk.

1066
01:04:21.984 --> 01:04:22.938
Chocolate.

1067
01:04:39.598 --> 01:04:40.513
Lorraine.

1068
01:04:41.414 --> 01:04:42.464
My density,

1069
01:04:43.245 --> 01:04:44.945
has popped me to you.

1070
01:04:45.883 --> 01:04:46.757
What?

1071
01:04:49.194 --> 01:04:50.662
What I meant to say...

1072
01:04:51.327 --> 01:04:52.027
was...

1073
01:04:52.125 --> 01:04:53.025
Wait a minute.

1074
01:04:53.050 --> 01:04:54.531
Don't I know you from somewhere?

1075
01:04:55.450 --> 01:04:56.450
Yes.

1076
01:04:56.798 --> 01:04:58.998
Yes. I am George.

1077
01:04:59.233 --> 01:05:01.052
George McFly.

1078
01:05:01.579 --> 01:05:03.046
I am your density.

1079
01:05:04.248 --> 01:05:05.248
I mean...

1080
01:05:06.959 --> 01:05:07.935
your destiny.

1081
01:05:11.380 --> 01:05:12.597
Hey McFly.

1082
01:05:14.510 --> 01:05:15.510
Geez...

1083
01:05:17.219 --> 01:05:19.213
I thought I told you never to come in here.

1084
01:05:22.641 --> 01:05:24.051
Well, it's going to cost you.

1085
01:05:25.117 --> 01:05:26.568
How much money you got on you?

1086
01:05:26.593 --> 01:05:27.293
Well...

1087
01:05:27.813 --> 01:05:29.339
How much do you want, Biff?

1088
01:05:38.157 --> 01:05:39.341
Alright, punk.

1089
01:05:39.825 --> 01:05:40.625
Now I am going...

1090
01:05:40.808 --> 01:05:42.170
Biff. What's that?

1091
01:05:49.293 --> 01:05:50.285
Calvin Klein.

1092
01:05:50.586 --> 01:05:52.237
Oh, my God, he is a dream.

1093
01:05:53.631 --> 01:05:55.482
Kid! Kid! Stop! Stop! Stop!

1094
01:05:55.507 --> 01:05:56.674
Hey!

1095
01:05:58.844 --> 01:05:59.928
I will get it back to you, alright?

1096
01:06:00.971 --> 01:06:02.170
You broke it!

1097
01:06:03.015 --> 01:06:04.218
Come back here!

1098
01:06:06.872 --> 01:06:08.366
Look at him go!

1099
01:06:09.858 --> 01:06:10.751
Get him!

1100
01:06:24.536 --> 01:06:26.301
To the car! Go! Go!

1101
01:06:33.003 --> 01:06:34.470
What's that thing he is on?

1102
01:06:34.495 --> 01:06:35.856
It's a board with wheels.

1103
01:06:35.881 --> 01:06:37.401
He is an absolute dream.

1104
01:06:37.426 --> 01:06:38.667
Come on, come on, come on!

1105
01:06:38.842 --> 01:06:40.385
Look out! Look out for the car!

1106
01:07:13.711 --> 01:07:14.745
I am going to ram him.

1107
01:07:22.928 --> 01:07:24.000
Shit!

1108
01:07:48.629 --> 01:07:49.839
Thanks a lot kid.

1109
01:07:51.466 --> 01:07:53.384
I am going to get that son of a bitch.

1110
01:07:53.968 --> 01:07:55.010
Where does he come from?

1111
01:07:55.094 --> 01:07:56.470
Yeah, where does he live?

1112
01:07:57.680 --> 01:07:58.917
I don't know,

1113
01:07:59.625 --> 01:08:01.171
but I am going to find out.

1114
01:08:07.020 --> 01:08:07.966
<i>Oh, my God.</i>

1115
01:08:08.724 --> 01:08:09.853
<i>They found me.</i>

1116
01:08:09.988 --> 01:08:11.762
<i>I don't know how, but they found me.</i>

1117
01:08:12.028 --> 01:08:13.295
<i>Run for it, Marty!</i>

1118
01:08:18.409 --> 01:08:19.338
<i>Oh, my God.</i>

1119
01:08:20.578 --> 01:08:21.525
<i>They found me.</i>

1120
01:08:21.588 --> 01:08:23.314
<i>I don't know how, but they found me.</i>

1121
01:08:23.581 --> 01:08:24.956
<i>Run for it Marty!</i>

1122
01:08:26.124 --> 01:08:26.890
Doc?

1123
01:08:28.086 --> 01:08:29.084
Hi Marty.

1124
01:08:29.533 --> 01:08:30.794
I didn't hear you come in.

1125
01:08:31.927 --> 01:08:33.201
Fascinating device,

1126
01:08:33.581 --> 01:08:34.663
this video unit.

1127
01:08:35.551 --> 01:08:36.619
Listen Doc.

1128
01:08:37.303 --> 01:08:39.914
You know, there is something I have not told you
about the night we made that tape.

1129
01:08:39.939 --> 01:08:40.950
Please, Marty, don't tell me.

1130
01:08:40.975 --> 01:08:42.367
No man should know too much
about his own destiny.

1131
01:08:42.392 --> 01:08:43.826
You don't understand.
I do understand.

1132
01:08:43.851 --> 01:08:45.158
If I know too much about my own future,

1133
01:08:45.183 --> 01:08:46.500
I can endanger my own existence.

1134
01:08:46.646 --> 01:08:48.280
Just as you have endangered yours.

1135
01:08:50.942 --> 01:08:52.559
You are right.
Now...

1136
01:08:52.944 --> 01:08:55.721
Let me show you my plan
for sending you home.

1137
01:08:55.905 --> 01:08:57.656
Please excuse the crudity of this model.

1138
01:08:57.740 --> 01:08:59.786
I didn't have time to build it to scale
or paint it.

1139
01:09:00.159 --> 01:09:01.661
It's good.
Thank you. Thank you.

1140
01:09:03.371 --> 01:09:04.379
Ok, now.

1141
01:09:04.593 --> 01:09:07.529
We run some industrial strength electrical
cable from the top...

1142
01:09:07.646 --> 01:09:08.814
of the clock tower,

1143
01:09:08.876 --> 01:09:11.972
down, suspending it over the street
between these two lamp posts.

1144
01:09:12.797 --> 01:09:14.244
Meanwhile, we have outfitted,

1145
01:09:14.441 --> 01:09:16.698
the time vehicle with this big pole
and hook,

1146
01:09:16.884 --> 01:09:19.845
which runs directly into the flux capacitor.

1147
01:09:20.763 --> 01:09:22.297
At the calculated moment,

1148
01:09:23.188 --> 01:09:24.168
you start off,

1149
01:09:24.469 --> 01:09:25.506
from down the street,

1150
01:09:25.530 --> 01:09:28.836
driving directly toward the cable
accelerating to 88 miles per hour.

1151
01:09:30.212 --> 01:09:33.589
According to the flyer at precisely
10:04 p.m this Saturday night,

1152
01:09:33.628 --> 01:09:35.471
lightning will strike the clock tower,

1153
01:09:35.495 --> 01:09:37.099
electrifying the cable,

1154
01:09:37.334 --> 01:09:39.585
just as the connecting hook makes contact

1155
01:09:39.615 --> 01:09:41.814
thereby sending 1.21 gigawatts,

1156
01:09:41.838 --> 01:09:43.243
into the flux capacitor

1157
01:09:43.619 --> 01:09:45.706
and sending you back to 1985.

1158
01:09:45.801 --> 01:09:46.788
Alright now.

1159
01:09:46.860 --> 01:09:47.823
Watch this.

1160
01:09:47.912 --> 01:09:49.529
You wind up the car and release it.

1161
01:09:51.711 --> 01:09:53.157
I will simulate the lightning.

1162
01:10:02.221 --> 01:10:03.022
Ready.

1163
01:10:13.149 --> 01:10:14.149
Set.

1164
01:10:19.322 --> 01:10:20.097
Release.

1165
01:10:38.966 --> 01:10:41.134
You are instilling me with
a lot of confidence Doc.

1166
01:10:41.159 --> 01:10:42.700
Don't worry.
I will take care of the lightning.

1167
01:10:42.725 --> 01:10:44.455
Just take care of your pop.

1168
01:10:46.432 --> 01:10:47.421
By the way,

1169
01:10:47.445 --> 01:10:49.134
what happened today?
Did he ask her out?

1170
01:10:49.464 --> 01:10:50.589
I think so.

1171
01:10:50.728 --> 01:10:51.770
What did she say?

1172
01:11:00.505 --> 01:11:02.256
It's your mom!
She is tracked you down!

1173
01:11:02.281 --> 01:11:04.133
Quick!
Let's cover the time machine.

1174
01:11:17.880 --> 01:11:18.619
Hi,

1175
01:11:19.364 --> 01:11:20.340
Cal... Marty.

1176
01:11:20.841 --> 01:11:22.159
Mom. Lorraine.

1177
01:11:23.724 --> 01:11:25.340
How did you know I was here?

1178
01:11:26.931 --> 01:11:27.835
I followed you.

1179
01:11:30.008 --> 01:11:31.335
This is my doc...

1180
01:11:31.360 --> 01:11:32.313
My uncle.

1181
01:11:32.842 --> 01:11:33.634
Doc...

1182
01:11:34.069 --> 01:11:34.957
Brown.

1183
01:11:35.815 --> 01:11:36.865
Hi.
Hi.

1184
01:11:40.152 --> 01:11:41.141
Marty listen,

1185
01:11:41.542 --> 01:11:43.521
this may seem a little forward,

1186
01:11:43.698 --> 01:11:45.598
but I was kind of wondering if you...

1187
01:11:46.699 --> 01:11:48.750
if-if you'd ask me to the...

1188
01:11:49.442 --> 01:11:51.965
Enchantment Under
the Sea dance on Saturday.

1189
01:11:54.359 --> 01:11:55.475
You mean...

1190
01:11:56.017 --> 01:11:57.442
You mean nobody has asked you?

1191
01:11:58.379 --> 01:11:59.415
No.

1192
01:12:00.432 --> 01:12:01.460
Not yet.

1193
01:12:03.175 --> 01:12:04.837
What about?
What about George?

1194
01:12:05.043 --> 01:12:06.743
George McFly?

1195
01:12:09.140 --> 01:12:12.214
He is kind of cute and all but...

1196
01:12:12.479 --> 01:12:13.384
not...

1197
01:12:13.894 --> 01:12:14.835
Well,

1198
01:12:15.818 --> 01:12:18.198
I think a man should be strong,

1199
01:12:20.067 --> 01:12:22.019
so he can stand up for himself,

1200
01:12:23.362 --> 01:12:25.014
and protect the woman he loves.

1201
01:12:30.211 --> 01:12:31.123
Don't you?

1202
01:12:33.205 --> 01:12:34.205
Yeah I...

1203
01:12:34.694 --> 01:12:36.904
I still don't understand.

1204
01:12:37.107 --> 01:12:39.817
How am I supposed to go
to the dance with her,

1205
01:12:40.004 --> 01:12:42.356
if she is already going
to the dance with you?

1206
01:12:42.840 --> 01:12:44.908
Because George,
she wants to go with you.

1207
01:12:45.593 --> 01:12:47.310
She just doesn't know it yet.

1208
01:12:47.595 --> 01:12:49.084
That's why we got to show her that you,

1209
01:12:49.249 --> 01:12:50.780
George McFly, are a fighter.

1210
01:12:50.805 --> 01:12:52.700
You are somebody who is
gonna stand up for yourself,

1211
01:12:52.725 --> 01:12:54.184
somebody who is gonna protect her.

1212
01:12:54.268 --> 01:12:56.979
Yeah, but I have never picked
a fight in my entire life.

1213
01:12:57.563 --> 01:12:59.715
Ok look, you are not going
to be picking a fight Dad.

1214
01:13:00.399 --> 01:13:02.034
Dad. Dad. Daddy-o.

1215
01:13:02.567 --> 01:13:04.651
You are coming to her rescue, right?

1216
01:13:05.071 --> 01:13:06.237
Ok, let's go over the plan again.

1217
01:13:06.322 --> 01:13:08.073
8:55, where are you going to be?

1218
01:13:08.157 --> 01:13:09.741
I am going to be at the dance.

1219
01:13:09.825 --> 01:13:10.953
Right.
And where am I going to be?

1220
01:13:10.978 --> 01:13:12.979
You are gonna be in the car with her.

1221
01:13:13.004 --> 01:13:14.555
Right, ok. So right around 9 o'clock

1222
01:13:14.580 --> 01:13:15.997
she is going to get very angry with me.

1223
01:13:16.082 --> 01:13:18.000
Why is she going to get angry with you?

1224
01:13:18.584 --> 01:13:20.978
Well because, George nice girls get angry

1225
01:13:21.003 --> 01:13:23.129
when guys take advantage of them.

1226
01:13:25.508 --> 01:13:27.509
You mean you are going
to go touch her on her...

1227
01:13:27.593 --> 01:13:28.123
No.

1228
01:13:28.147 --> 01:13:29.270
No, George.

1229
01:13:29.547 --> 01:13:30.247
Look.

1230
01:13:30.778 --> 01:13:32.002
It's just an act,

1231
01:13:32.026 --> 01:13:32.737
right?

1232
01:13:33.140 --> 01:13:34.212
Ok. So...

1233
01:13:34.236 --> 01:13:36.743
9 o'clock you are strolling through
the parking lot.

1234
01:13:37.061 --> 01:13:38.166
You see us...

1235
01:13:38.564 --> 01:13:40.294
struggling in the car.

1236
01:13:40.573 --> 01:13:41.634
You walk up,

1237
01:13:41.913 --> 01:13:43.658
you open the door and you say...

1238
01:13:45.400 --> 01:13:47.051
Your line, George.

1239
01:13:50.366 --> 01:13:51.229
Hey you,

1240
01:13:51.253 --> 01:13:53.201
get your damn hands off her!

1241
01:13:55.538 --> 01:13:57.085
You really think I ought to swear?

1242
01:13:57.354 --> 01:13:59.464
Yes, definitely.
Goddamn it George, swear.

1243
01:13:59.750 --> 01:14:00.976
Ok. So now.

1244
01:14:01.001 --> 01:14:01.812
You come up.

1245
01:14:01.936 --> 01:14:03.059
You punch me in the stomach.

1246
01:14:03.084 --> 01:14:04.708
I am out for the count, right?

1247
01:14:04.922 --> 01:14:06.370
And you and Lorraine live,

1248
01:14:06.453 --> 01:14:07.982
happily ever after.

1249
01:14:08.037 --> 01:14:10.247
You make it sound so easy.

1250
01:14:10.511 --> 01:14:11.249
I just...

1251
01:14:11.273 --> 01:14:12.971
I wish I was not so scared.

1252
01:14:13.055 --> 01:14:14.539
George, there is nothing to be scared of.

1253
01:14:14.564 --> 01:14:16.307
All it takes is a little self-confidence.

1254
01:14:17.017 --> 01:14:17.756
You know,

1255
01:14:17.912 --> 01:14:19.367
if you put your mind to it,

1256
01:14:19.812 --> 01:14:21.271
you can accomplish anything.

1257
01:14:23.899 --> 01:14:26.109
<i>Hill Valley area weather
this Saturday night.</i>

1258
01:14:26.208 --> 01:14:27.391
<i>Mostly clear,</i>

1259
01:14:27.415 --> 01:14:28.910
<i>with some scattered clouds.</i>

1260
01:14:29.339 --> 01:14:31.048
<i>Lows tonight in the upper 40s.</i>

1261
01:14:31.120 --> 01:14:32.738
Are you sure about this storm?

1262
01:14:33.826 --> 01:14:35.977
Since when can weathermen
predict the weather,

1263
01:14:36.078 --> 01:14:37.296
let alone the future?

1264
01:14:38.429 --> 01:14:40.766
You know Marty, I am going
to be very sad to see you go.

1265
01:14:41.250 --> 01:14:42.624
You have really made
a difference in my life.

1266
01:14:42.652 --> 01:14:44.074
You have given me something to shoot for.

1267
01:14:44.839 --> 01:14:46.076
Just knowing,

1268
01:14:46.100 --> 01:14:48.535
that I am going to be around to see 1985.

1269
01:14:49.008 --> 01:14:50.825
That I am going to succeed in this!

1270
01:14:51.010 --> 01:14:53.387
That I am going to have a chance
to travel through time!

1271
01:14:59.963 --> 01:15:02.747
It's going to be really hard waiting
30 years before I can talk to you

1272
01:15:02.772 --> 01:15:04.534
about everything that's happened
in the past few days.

1273
01:15:05.816 --> 01:15:07.401
I am really going to miss you Marty.

1274
01:15:09.737 --> 01:15:10.979
I am really going to miss you.

1275
01:15:15.951 --> 01:15:17.484
Doc, about the future...

1276
01:15:17.611 --> 01:15:18.611
No!

1277
01:15:18.844 --> 01:15:19.805
Marty!

1278
01:15:20.414 --> 01:15:24.209
We have already agreed that having information
about the future can be extremely dangerous.

1279
01:15:24.234 --> 01:15:25.735
Even if your intentions are good,

1280
01:15:25.878 --> 01:15:27.537
it can backfire drastically.

1281
01:15:29.148 --> 01:15:30.357
Whatever you have got to tell me,

1282
01:15:30.382 --> 01:15:32.474
I will find out through
the natural course of time.

1283
01:15:34.512 --> 01:15:35.771
Dear Dr. Brown.

1284
01:15:37.223 --> 01:15:39.082
On the night that I go back in time,

1285
01:15:40.142 --> 01:15:41.193
you will be...

1286
01:15:42.478 --> 01:15:43.467
shot...

1287
01:15:43.803 --> 01:15:44.948
by terrorists.

1288
01:15:45.898 --> 01:15:48.417
Please take whatever
precautions are necessary

1289
01:15:48.442 --> 01:15:50.302
to prevent this terrible disaster.

1290
01:15:52.321 --> 01:15:53.330
Your friend,

1291
01:15:55.074 --> 01:15:56.074
Marty.

1292
01:16:05.751 --> 01:16:07.142
Evening, Dr. Brown.

1293
01:16:07.608 --> 01:16:08.671
What's with the wire?

1294
01:16:08.796 --> 01:16:09.928
Oh just...

1295
01:16:10.348 --> 01:16:11.862
a little weather experiment.

1296
01:16:13.551 --> 01:16:14.551
What you got under here?

1297
01:16:14.635 --> 01:16:15.635
No!
Don't touch that!

1298
01:16:15.660 --> 01:16:17.754
Some new, specialized
weather sensing equipment.

1299
01:16:18.597 --> 01:16:20.307
You got a permit for that?

1300
01:16:21.328 --> 01:16:22.720
Of course I do.

1301
01:16:29.650 --> 01:16:31.977
Just a second.
Let me see if I can find it here.

1302
01:17:24.514 --> 01:17:25.911
Do you mind if we...

1303
01:17:26.839 --> 01:17:27.796
park...

1304
01:17:28.234 --> 01:17:29.441
for a while?

1305
01:17:30.311 --> 01:17:32.412
That's a great idea.
I would love to park.

1306
01:17:33.481 --> 01:17:35.983
Marty, I am almost 18 years old.

1307
01:17:36.275 --> 01:17:38.193
It's not like I have never parked before.

1308
01:17:38.986 --> 01:17:39.850
What?

1309
01:17:40.821 --> 01:17:43.323
Marty, you seem so nervous.
Is something wrong?

1310
01:17:43.908 --> 01:17:44.822
No.

1311
01:17:45.973 --> 01:17:46.720
No.

1312
01:17:51.864 --> 01:17:53.809
Lorraine, what are you doing?

1313
01:17:54.835 --> 01:17:57.082
I swiped it from the old
lady's liquor cabinet.

