1393
01:22:22.228 --> 01:22:23.382
Biff stop it!

1394
01:22:24.730 --> 01:22:26.281
Biff, you will break his arm!

1395
01:22:28.484 --> 01:22:29.534
Biff no!

1396
01:22:30.569 --> 01:22:31.762
Give me a hand here Reginald.

1397
01:22:34.198 --> 01:22:36.091
Dammit man!
I sliced my hand!

1398
01:22:36.575 --> 01:22:38.034
Whose are these?
Mine.

1399
01:22:38.118 --> 01:22:39.536
Thanks.
Thanks a lot.

1400
01:22:41.372 --> 01:22:42.822
You are going to break his arm!

1401
01:22:43.814 --> 01:22:44.490
Biff!

1402
01:22:44.884 --> 01:22:45.572
Biff,

1403
01:22:45.596 --> 01:22:46.934
leave him alone!

1404
01:22:47.127 --> 01:22:48.987
Let him go!
Let him go!

1405
01:23:22.746 --> 01:23:24.130
Are you ok?

1406
01:23:44.393 --> 01:23:46.028
Who is that guy?

1407
01:23:46.655 --> 01:23:47.904
That's George McFly.

1408
01:23:51.859 --> 01:23:53.702
That's George McFly?

1409
01:23:54.266 --> 01:23:55.432
Excuse me.

1410
01:24:06.360 --> 01:24:07.461
The storm.

1411
01:24:10.206 --> 01:24:12.672
Hey guys, you got to get back
in there and finish the dance.

1412
01:24:12.796 --> 01:24:14.213
Hey, man.
Look at Marvin's hand.

1413
01:24:14.298 --> 01:24:16.692
He can't play with his hand like that,
and we can't play without him.

1414
01:24:16.717 --> 01:24:17.581
Yeah, well. Look...

1415
01:24:17.792 --> 01:24:19.037
Marvin you got to play.

1416
01:24:19.097 --> 01:24:21.488
See, that's where they kiss for
the first time on the dance floor.

1417
01:24:21.513 --> 01:24:23.222
And if there is no music,
they can't dance.

1418
01:24:23.307 --> 01:24:24.599
If they can't dance, they can't kiss.

1419
01:24:24.683 --> 01:24:26.760
If they can't kiss,
they can't fall in love and I am history.

1420
01:24:26.761 --> 01:24:28.222
Hey man, the dance is over,

1421
01:24:28.363 --> 01:24:31.079
unless you know somebody else
that can play the guitar.

1422
01:24:38.322 --> 01:24:40.840
<i>This is for all you lovers out there.</i>

1423
01:24:54.797 --> 01:24:56.631
George, are not you going to kiss me?

1424
01:24:56.715 --> 01:24:58.216
I don't know.

1425
01:25:00.010 --> 01:25:02.136
Scram McFly.
I am cutting in.

1426
01:25:15.693 --> 01:25:17.164
Hey boy, you alright?

1427
01:25:18.821 --> 01:25:19.979
I can't play.

1428
01:25:20.364 --> 01:25:21.447
George!

1429
01:25:38.924 --> 01:25:39.974
George!

1430
01:25:41.593 --> 01:25:42.454
George.

1431
01:25:45.806 --> 01:25:46.969
Excuse me.

1432
01:26:34.313 --> 01:26:35.385
Yeah.

1433
01:26:35.531 --> 01:26:36.845
Man that was good.

1434
01:26:36.915 --> 01:26:38.278
Let's do another one.

1435
01:26:38.317 --> 01:26:40.234
No.
I got to go.

1436
01:26:40.326 --> 01:26:41.433
Come on man.

1437
01:26:41.457 --> 01:26:43.528
Let's do something that really cooks.

1438
01:26:43.906 --> 01:26:44.811
Something...

1439
01:26:45.296 --> 01:26:46.648
that cooks.

1440
01:26:52.281 --> 01:26:53.222
Alright.

1441
01:26:58.212 --> 01:26:58.954
<i>Alright.</i>

1442
01:27:00.506 --> 01:27:02.454
<i>Alright this is...
this is an oldie...</i>

1443
01:27:03.274 --> 01:27:04.178
<i>but...</i>

1444
01:27:05.928 --> 01:27:06.708
<i>Well it...</i>

1445
01:27:07.161 --> 01:27:09.373
<i>it's an oldie where I come from.</i>

1446
01:27:11.409 --> 01:27:13.660
Alright guys, listen, this is a blues riff in B.

1447
01:27:13.685 --> 01:27:16.428
Watch me for the changes,
and try and keep up ok?

1448
01:27:59.447 --> 01:28:02.251
Hey George, I heard you laid out Biff.
Nice going.

1449
01:28:02.276 --> 01:28:04.569
George, you ever think of running
for class president?

1450
01:28:25.674 --> 01:28:26.829
Chuck!
Chuck!

1451
01:28:26.986 --> 01:28:28.244
It's Marvin.

1452
01:28:28.594 --> 01:28:30.752
Your cousin, Marvin Berry.

1453
01:28:31.263 --> 01:28:34.015
You know that new sound
you are looking for?

1454
01:28:34.099 --> 01:28:35.847
Well, listen to this.

1455
01:29:44.545 --> 01:29:46.606
<i>I guess you guys are not
ready for that yet.</i>

1456
01:29:48.942 --> 01:29:50.568
<i>But your kids are going to love it.</i>

1457
01:29:54.722 --> 01:29:55.604
Lorraine.

1458
01:29:56.182 --> 01:29:58.367
Marty, that was very interesting music.

1459
01:29:59.651 --> 01:30:00.635
Yeah.

1460
01:30:00.916 --> 01:30:02.497
I... I hope you don't mind,

1461
01:30:02.522 --> 01:30:04.564
but George asked
if he could take me home.

1462
01:30:04.589 --> 01:30:05.638
Great! Good!

1463
01:30:05.779 --> 01:30:07.135
Good, Lorraine.

1464
01:30:07.819 --> 01:30:09.236
I had a feeling about you two.

1465
01:30:09.696 --> 01:30:11.155
I have a feeling too.

1466
01:30:12.031 --> 01:30:13.307
Listen, I got to go,

1467
01:30:13.491 --> 01:30:15.820
but I wanted to tell you that it's been...

1468
01:30:17.021 --> 01:30:18.103
educational.

1469
01:30:19.247 --> 01:30:20.907
Marty, will we ever see you again?

1470
01:30:22.800 --> 01:30:23.909
I guarantee it.

1471
01:30:24.210 --> 01:30:25.258
Well Marty...

1472
01:30:25.759 --> 01:30:28.285
I want to thank you
for all your good advice so...

1473
01:30:28.714 --> 01:30:29.748
I will never forget it.

1474
01:30:30.758 --> 01:30:32.042
Right, George.

1475
01:30:33.720 --> 01:30:34.740
Well...

1476
01:30:35.841 --> 01:30:37.322
good luck you guys.

1477
01:30:41.227 --> 01:30:42.405
One other thing.

1478
01:30:43.153 --> 01:30:45.094
If you guys ever have kids,

1479
01:30:45.291 --> 01:30:47.709
and one of them,
when he is eight years old,

1480
01:30:47.734 --> 01:30:50.736
